          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-02-12 15:12:10" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a document or book containing wise sayings (as in the phrase ἡ σοφία τοῦ θεοῦ ‘the Wisdom of God,’ {S:04201104900010}, a possible reference to the OT or to apocryphal wisdom literature, possibly even a book which has been lost)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>Wisdom</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>If one understands ἡ σοφία τοῦ θεοῦ as being a reference to a book, one could translate the statement in {S:04201104900010} as ‘for this reason, the book entitled The Wisdom of God has the words: …’ On the other hand, the phrase ἡ σοφία τοῦ θεοῦ in {S:04201104900010} may mean merely ‘God’s wisdom’ ({D:32.32}), and therefore this expression in {S:04201104900010} could be rendered as ‘God in his wisdom said’ or ‘God, who is wise, said.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
